President Trump gave a speech at the Greenbrier Resort in West Virginia, where he thanked the governor and first lady of the state. He also mentioned that he spent the last three days interviewing Supreme Court Justices and will announce his pick on Monday. He praised the golfers in attendance and recognized the importance of the military and veterans. He discussed the need for border security and the importance of ICE. He also highlighted the economic progress the country has made and the efforts to support the military and veterans. The President also recognized Woody Williams, a veteran who received the Congressional Medal of Honor, and Christine Pusateri, a Gold Star Spouse. He concluded by pledging to renew the bonds of love and loyalty that unite Americans and to expand the blessings of liberty, prosperity, and justice to all citizens.